args:
Having driven off the dragons, the party faces a
new group of fiends. At their limits, they are
saved by Emile and the people of Grams.
The next day, the prince parts from his siblings
and turns to the desert with hope in his heart.
We managed to hold them off... Nnngh...
Y-yes, thank you. Just a bit winded...
And no wonder; we've been fighting\nnonstop, with not even the time to lick\nour wounds from the battle with Xenos.
The Dyrenell soldiers are also exhausted.\nLooks like it's time to rest and regroup.
So let's all get back and...
That's the same sound as before!
It's another horde of fiends, though at least\nthere aren't dragons with them this time.
But there's more than before,\nand we're already exhausted!
We have to fight. We have to protect them.
But we can't very well sit here and watch\nthe citizens of Grams be slaughtered.
The fiends have come again!\nSomeone save us!
It's over! We were destined to die!
I suggest you spend less time bemoaning\nyour fates and RUN LIKE YOUR VERY LIVES\nDEPEND ON IT!
*pant* *pant* Can't...go on...\nWe've got kids...sick...elderly...\nWe can't...keep running...
Then take up a weapon and fight, churl!\nIf we all do the same, perhaps even you\npathetic dunderheads can make a stand!
But we're just a bunch of regular citizens!\nWe don't know how to fight!
Well then what are you going to do?!\nYou can't expect someone to always\nshow up and rescue you!
You're right... No one is coming to\nsave us...even those swaggering church\nfellows were slain...
We can't count on the government, either...\nIt's hopeless. We should just give up.
That's right. It's important for people like\nus to know when to surrender to fate.
Our homes are gone. Our city is gone.\nMaybe it's time to...
So that means you're giving up?
Everything we built has gone to waste!\nWhat's even left to live for?
No matter what we do or how hard we\npush, it's all pointless in the end.
But I suppose a haughty ruler like you\nwouldn't understand such things.
Surrender is not so simple a matter!
I've always wanted to be a great king—\none adored by his people who could\nsolve every problem himself.

But I had no talent. Couldn't use a sword.
Couldn't chant a spell. I even studied
alchemy for nigh-on hundreds of hours
and could not grasp its secrets.

I've a bad memory and am slow to pick
things up. Additionally, I'm hopelessly
outmatched when my siblings speak on
matters of the kingdom.

Realizing the straightforward approach
would not work, I turned to deception,
threats, and trickery—yet in the end,
I failed even with them.
A great king? Ha! I wasn't worthy to rule\nover an anthill. And with this decided,\nI simply...gave up.
That's why if I ever find myself in danger,\nI'll abandon you people and flee!
While a great king might never do such a\nthing, I am no such great king, and it's no\nskin off my apple to do exactly that!
You spoke at such great length just to\nsay you'd ABANDON us?!
That's right! I'm an expert at giving up!\nThe sword? Magic? Tactics? Politics?\nI've given up on ALL of them.
BUT! Unlike you people, I have never once\ngiven up on something without at least\nattempting it.

I practiced the blade until I vomited blood!
I studied for days on end without sleep!
And not once did I EVER say a thing I had
never attempted was impossible!
Which means you people haven't earned\nthe right to give up! Not yet, anyway!
I speak from years of experience\nwhen I say it is too soon to give up.

So go ahead! Stand here whimpering and
perish in a sad puddle of your own make!
But don't think for a second this was the
only choice afforded to you!
What you people are talking about is\nnothing more than suicide!
We shall follow you through all, sir!
Damn it all. I don't want to go...
We have no right to give up.
I sure as hell hope somebody has a plan\nhere, because I'm fresh outta ideas!
It's Emile! And...the citizens of Grams?!
Go, everyone! Rend them to pieces!
I can't believe this is happening...
*sigh* I thought I was so dead.
*sigh* You put the people you were meant\nto protect on the front lines? Terrible.
And not the people of his own lands,\neither. I fear this could well turn into\nan international incident.
But...but there was no other way!
Indeed, there was no other way—and I do\nnot think anyone could have thought of\nthis other than you.

We were caught up in the orthodox
conception of protecting the people
and could never have devised such a
strategy. We owe you a debt, Emile.
I never thought a day would come\nin which YOU saved my life.
Heh... Ha ha! Aaaaaah ha ha ha!
BWAAAAAAAH HA HA HA HA HA!\nAT LONG LAST, MY TIME IS COME!
Well, you certainly wasted no time letting\nthat go to your head...
Oh, let us allow it just this once. Not only\ndid he not give up, he actually did well.
Are you all really returning to Alberia?
Yes. No matter his recent deeds, I'm not\nentirely comfortable leaving the people of\nGrams in Emile's grubby little hands.
Furthermore, I need to consult with the\nking of Grams, and also have concerns\nabout Chanzelia.
Governance is most necessary when\nmatters both within and without the\nnation are in turmoil, after all.
Now is the time when we must fulfill \nour responsibilities as royalty.
I see. Take good care of Alberia, then.
It is our home, and we will see it safe.\nNow let us be off.
I, um... Look, just don't die, all right?
I won't be satisfied if I can't force you\nto submit to me!

I don't know what-all about this Progenitor
person, but if they manage to kill you,
know that I'll drag you back from hell
and kill you again myself!
So strike this dastard down, save the\nworld, and come home.
Then—and only then—will I suffer you\nto grovel in the dirt before me!
Heh. All right, Emile. I promise.
Good. Oh, and never forget all the thanks\nyou owe me. Got it?!
Next stop, the desert! I hope it's hot, hot,\nhooooot!
That much heat would likely exhaust our\nstrength, save for you. Still, I must admit\na bit of curiosity about the place.
Well, it's Gatov's former home, right?\nMaybe he can tell us about it.
...That wasteland to the east was once\na thriving nation called Lefkos.
After Sheila and I were forced to abandon\nit, it transformed into a desert.
That sounds like a rather sudden change of\nenvironment. Was it the work of a dragon?
Without people to govern and protect\nthem, the lands grew rough and wild.

If you trace the origins of Lefkos sinking
into the sand, it all leads back to my
responsibility for not being able to protect
my kingdom or people.
Feels like there's some backstory here.\nYou gonna be okay?
I always knew the day would come when I\nwould have to face my past. It is well and\nproper that it should happen now.
And in this fallen kingdom of Lefkos will\nwe find a way to awaken the powers\nof the Five Greatwyrms.
We must not fail in this, for it is our only\nmeans to stand against the Progenitor.
The possibility of victory isn't dead yet!
